
REQUIREMENTS
============
It is assumed that the user has a UNIX-like shell, and the NPM command line utility.

BUILD
=====
First, install all of the node depencencies:
1. navigate, in terminal, to the root directory of the git repository
2. run: `npm install`

Then, the local database will need to be constructed:
1. still in the base of the repository:
2. run `./node_modules/knex/bin/cli.js migrate:latest`

DONE.

RUN
===
To run, navigate to the root directory of the repo.
Then, run: `npm start`

